JMC Notes 0703

Underscore.js

Methods:
_.compact
_.findWhere (returns just the first match)
_.where (returns all matches)
_.pluck (extracts list of property values)
_.uniq (rips out duplicates)
_.sortBy


- Utilities for arrays and objects
- "git checkout ." wipes out local repo w online one
- slots[] is array
- Version info:
	"_.VERSION" for underscore.js
	"$().jquery" for jQuery
- Library uses "_" for namespacing.  Avoids conflicts
- _.compact
- Falsy values: false, null, 0, "", undefined, NaN
- Empty objects/arrays are considered truthy
- underscore methods are non-destructive; almost all...
- _.findWhere failes if null's are present in the list
- Adding property to array: arr[x].<property> = <value>


Namespacing & Privacy

- Encapsulation: avoiding naming conflicts and hiding data
- "Revealing Module Pattern": put all code in function
- "Immediately Invoked Function Expression" (IIFE):  can define a function
  and immediately calling it at the same time
  ex) var app = ( function(){ <func definition> } )();

- Keep document ready section clean; App.init(), App.setupEvent(), App.renderTable() are examples
  keeps entry points clear/clean
